commitResults.messageBody:
When performing undo/redo via menu items or keyboard shortcuts,
CommandHistorySelector#selectLast would not be called because
it was originally assumed that all commands would go through
CommandBox.

This patch shifts the #selectLast call to LogicManager because
commands go through that regardless of UI.

commitResults.messageBody:
The parser now deals with non-integer and integer input separately. This
allows for better error messages to be raised to the user to explain why
the entered preamble used in index values may be failing.

This commit also separates non-integer input to throw an
illegalargumentexception instead of a parseexception, which is now
reserved for integer input that fails (<=0, > range of list, etc)
